    "source_map": {
      "adc.*": "Anchored to Song et al. ISCA 2025 Table 2 shared 7b ADC point (0.30 mm2, 512 units) and the paper's 100 ns / 128-column readout window. The remaining 1b-6b and 8b-16b points are rough estimates obtained by applying the original science_adi9405_v1_neurosim ADC scaling ratios to that 7b anchor.",
      "dac.*": "Anchored to Song et al. ISCA 2025 Table 2 WL DRV total (0.02 mm2, 297.71 mW over 64x512 one-bit drivers). The remaining multi-bit DAC points are rough estimates obtained by applying the original science_adi9405_v1_neurosim DAC scaling ratios to that 1b anchor.",
      "array.*": "Anchored to Song et al. ISCA 2025 Table 2 analog RRAM array total (0.048 mm2, 60.78 mW over 512 arrays of 64x128) and the 10 ns VMM statement in the paper text. The area/energy are scaled 2x to approximate a 128x128 estimator macro.",
      "analog_periphery.snh.*": "Anchored to Song et al. ISCA 2025 Table 2 S&H total (6e-5 mm2, 12e-6 mW over 512 units).",
      "analog_periphery.tia.*": "Set to 0.0 for this Song-analog/SRAM-CIM library because Song et al. ISCA 2025, ASADI, and ISAAC do not provide isolated TIA coefficients and we do not want inherited proxy values to dominate the readout path.",
      "analog_periphery.mux.*": "Set to 0.0 for this Song-analog/SRAM-CIM library because Song et al. ISCA 2025, ASADI, and ISAAC do not provide isolated mux coefficients and we do not want inherited proxy values to dominate the readout path.",
      "analog_periphery.io_buffers.*": "Kept from the original science_adi9405_v1_neurosim library.",
      "analog_periphery.subarray_switches.*": "Kept from the original science_adi9405_v1_neurosim library.",
      "analog_periphery.write_drivers.*": "Kept at the original zero default; WL driver effects are already absorbed into dac.* via the Song Table 2 anchor.",
      "soc.buffers_add.*": "Kept from the original science_adi9405_v1_neurosim backend, but interpreted as the post-ADC adder only (reference/final_ppa_summary.csv row buffers_add_unit), not a folded buffer+quantize block.",
      "digital.*": "Copied unchanged from the original science_adi9405_v1_neurosim library.",
      "memory.*": "Copied unchanged from the original science_adi9405_v1_neurosim library.",
      "leakage_power.*": "Copied from the original science_adi9405_v1_neurosim library, except buffers_add_nw now follows buffers_add_unit only."
    },
    "source_notes": {
      "paper_refs": [
        "reference/Song 等 - 2025 - Hybrid SLC-MLC RRAM Mixed-Signal Processing-in-Memory Architecture for Transformer Acceleration via.pdf",
        "reference/Programming memristor arrays with arbitrarily high precision for analog computing  Science.pdf",
        "reference/science.adi9405_sm.pdf"
      ],
      "library_construction": "Analog-only Song transplant on top of the original science_adi9405_v1_neurosim backend. The original digital, memory, control, and SRAM-CIM assumptions are preserved; only the analog ReRAM front-end is replaced with Song-anchored values.",
      "song_table2_analog_cycle_ns": 100.0,
      "song_table2_array_vmm_ns": 10.0,
      "caveats": [
        "This is not a full HyFlexPIM reproduction.",
        "The estimator cannot represent Song's rectangular 64x128 analog array directly, so the array macro is approximated as a 128x128 macro by doubling the per-array area and energy anchors.",
        "Song reports shared 6b/7b ADC hardware explicitly; the library uses the 7b point as the anchor and derives 1b-6b and 8b-16b by ratio-scaling from the original NeuroSim-based library.",
        "The digital/non-stationary path remains SRAM-CIM / DC / CACTI based, following the original library rather than Song's digital-RRAM backend."
      ]
    }
  }
